dc_description_s: This data set contains imagery from the National Agriculture Imagery Program (NAIP). NAIP acquires digital ortho imagery during the agricultural growing seasons in the continental U.S.. A primary goal of the NAIP program is to enable availability of ortho imagery within one year of acquisition. Only the following counties have 2004 NAIP imagery available: Ashland, Barron, Brown, Buffalo, Burnett, Chippewa, Clark, Crawford, Dane, Dunn, Eau Claire, Grant, Jackson, Kewaunee, La Crosse, Manitowoc, Monroe, Pepin, Pierce, Polk, Richland, Rock, Rusk, Saint Croix, Sauk, Sawyer, Shawano, Sheboygan, Trempealeau, Vernon, Walworth, Washburn, Winnebago, WoodTrue color, orthorectified imagery. Timing: Imagery acquired between June 20th and August 30th 2004. Resolution: 2 m. Accuracy: +/- 3% when compared to a Mosaicked Digital Orthophoto Quadrangle. This imagery is NOT intended to be used for purposes requiring a high degree of spatial accuracy.
dc_title_s: NAIP Natural Color Aerial Mosaics (UTM), WI 2004
